.TH DATHUNDERBOLT 1 "2025-12-31" "dumbass-tree" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dathunderbolt \- Thunderbolt authorization helper (boltctl wrapper)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dathunderbolt
[--dry-run] [-v] [--yes]
.I <command>
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show controller security, boltd status, and a device list.
.TP
.B list
List Thunderbolt devices (including unauthorized ones).
.TP
.B domains
Show Thunderbolt domains/controllers.
.TP
.B authorize <uuid>
Authorize a device (temporary; does not store).
.TP
.B enroll <uuid>
Authorize and remember a device (stores it in boltd database).
.TP
.B forget <uuid>
Forget a previously enrolled device.
.TP
.B info <uuid>
Show details about a device.
.SH DESCRIPTION
dathunderbolt is a dumbass-friendly wrapper around boltctl/boltd for authorizing Thunderbolt devices.
.SH SEE ALSO
boltctl(1), boltd(8)
